Overall, the health coaching sessions will focus on utilising principles of behaviour change and self-regulation to assist participants with:
Increasing physical activity: Health coaches will assist participants to develop a tailored physical activity plan suitable to their individual lifestyle preferences;
Decreasing sedentary behaviour: Participants will be encouraged to increase daily incidental physical activity and decrease sitting time;
Achieving their health-related goals: The health coach will provide ongoing support and motivation to help participants achieve their personal physical activity and health-related goals. Health coaches will continually review participant progress with achieving their goals and assist with adjusting goals if necessary or as desired by the participant.
